SIMPLE: underdo
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underdo
<hw>Un`der*do"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To do less than
is requisite or proper; -- opposed to <ant>overdo</ant>.</def>
<rj><au>Grew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underdo</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Underdo
<hw>Un`der*do"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To do less thoroughly than is
requisite; specifically, to cook insufficiently; <as>as, to
<ex>underdo</ex> the meat</as>; -- opposed to
<contr>overdo</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underdoer</ent>⟦br⟧
